div.note:
These are the Five Roots [of Goodness] (wugen
                    五根; 
                        pañcendriyāṇi
                    ), which
                    are also part of the Thirty-seven Factors of Enlightenment.

These are the Five Powers (wuli
                    五力; 
                        pañca-balāni
                    ) that are
                    obtained through the cultivation of the Five Roots [of Goodness], and, just like
                    them, part of the Thirty-seven Factors of Enlightenment.

These are the Seven Limbs of Awakening
                        (qi juefen
                    七覺分; 
                        saptabodhyaṅgāni
                    ), which are part of the Thirty-seven Factors of
                        Enlightenment.

The list from Correct View to Correct Concentration comprises the Eightfold Correct Path (ba zhengdao
                    八正道; 
                        āryāṣṭāṅgikamārga
                    ), which is also part of the Thirty-seven Factors of
                    Enlightenment.

These are the Six Perfections (liu boluomi
                    六波羅蜜; 
                        ṣaṭpāramitā
                    ).
                    Note that this passage (T#397, 13: 50b16–19) is also engraved on the cliff at
                    Mount Hongding (HDS 2).
